@page "/privacy-policy-eng"

<div class="container" style="height: 100vh; align-content: center;">
    <h3>Privacy Policy – Plan Picker</h3>

    <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> June 3, 2025</p>

    <p>
        Plan Picker ("we", "our", or "the app") respects the privacy of its users. This privacy policy explains how we collect, use, and share information through our mobile application.
    </p>

    <p>
        <strong>Information We Collect:</strong><br>
        The app may automatically collect information, including but not limited to:<br>
        - Device type and operating system<br>
        - IP address<br>
        - App usage data<br>
        - Mobile identifiers (such as the Google Advertising ID - AAID)
    </p>

    <p>
        <strong>Ads:</strong><br>
        We use Google AdMob as our advertising provider. AdMob may collect and use data to show personalized or non-personalized ads, depending on the user's region.<br>
        More information: <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" target="_blank">https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads</a>
    </p>

    <p>
        <strong>User Consent:</strong><br>
        In certain regions (such as the European Union or California), we may display a consent request to comply with local regulations (such as GDPR or CCPA).<br>
        Users can choose between personalized or non-personalized ads.
    </p>

    <p>
        <strong>Security:</strong><br>
        We are committed to protecting user information. We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures, although no method of transmission or storage is completely secure.
    </p>

    <p>
        <strong>Changes to This Policy:</strong><br>
        We reserve the right to modify this privacy policy at any time. Any changes will be published within the app or on an accessible website.
    </p>

    <p>
        <strong>Contact:</strong><br>
        If you have questions or concerns about this privacy policy, you can contact us at:<br>
        alberto.morcillo.developer@gmail.com
    </p>

    <button style="border: none;
    background: inherit;
    float: right;" @onclick="Regresar">
    Return
    </button>
</div>



